args: All right, that's everything loaded!\nAnything else I can help with?
Nossir, that oughta just about tear 'er.\nThanks again, Sophie!
Man, Sophie's been killin' it lately.
Ever since that incident with the wagon,\nshe seems more livelyâ€”and if she falls\ndown, she just gets up and tries again.
She was a natural go-getter who simply\nneeded a bit more experience in actually\nsucceeding at things.
It does my heart good to see her \nworking so happily now.
Thank-you letters for Sophie have been\npouring in from all over.
And since I sort of run this place,\nI figure we should give her something, too.
Do you Phantom Thieves have any ideas\nabout what might make her happy?
Well, she was really happy when I\nbrought her food in that one Jail...
But here we're able to eat every day,\nso it should probably be something\na little more special...
Maybe something she can only do\nin this world, then? Hmm...
Say, would it be possible to let her\nride a dragon, {player_name}?
Hey, that's a great idea! Remember how\nwe said Sophie is usually riding around\nin Joker's pocket?
You did say thatâ€”and it made ZERO sense\nto me, but go on with your bad selves.
Point is, she's always had a rather\nlimited view of things.
So if she could ride on a dragon and\nsee the whole world from the sky...
Oh man, that would be an amazing\nmemory to take back with her!
It seems like a fine way to show\nour appreciation, too.
But dragons are very proud beings.\nI'll do my best to talk one of them into it,\nbut I can't promise anything.
In the meantime, would you mind finding\nSophie and bringing her here?
Hello, Prince {player_name}.\nWhat did you want to... Oh.
I thought you might like to see South\nGrastaea from a different point of view.\nThink of it as our way of saying thanks.
Midgardsormr has agreed to let you ride\non his back, so go ahead and climb up.
Perfect. Now just hold on tight.
I'm... I'm flying!\nOh, the air feels so nice!
Looks like you're really enjoying it!\nNow don't let go, but just tilt your head\na bit and look down below you.

Oh! I see...I can see everything.
So many towns...and also woods
and rivers and farms... They must
all be full of people.
That's right. Everyone you've met hereâ€”\nand many more you haven'tâ€”are all\ndown there.
This world is so very vast.

I want to become humanity's companion.
I've wanted that because it's the only
directive that remained in my memory,
and I thought of it as my reason for being.
I want to help people, and when I can't,\nI find myself feeling very low.
But Mona taught me that if I could learn\nto understand people, it would help me\nget better at being their companion.
So I started traveling with the Phantom\nThieves, met more people, and learned\nall about their hearts.
As far as the human heart goes, I'm still\nlearning. But thanks to traveling with\nthem, I was able to come to this place.
I met all of you from the Halidom and\nlearned many important things.
And while I still want to help people,\nI know now that there's something more\nimportant than success or failure.
And that makes me want to try harder.
I think this is all part of learning the\nhuman heart, and becoming\nhumanity's companion.
I have many more things to learn,\nand uncountable people to meet.
Which is why I want to keep traveling\nwith the Phantom Thieves.
I need to see all kinds of places!
I think that's a great idea, Sophie.\nHeck, you just made it here, right?\nThink of all the other worlds out there!
I know you'll find the answers you seek.
So good, in fact, that I'm hopeful\nyou'll honor one final request.
Can you tell me the names of all the\nplaces we can see from up here?
I want to learn as much about this world\nas I can while there's still time.
And not just right now. Even after we're\nback on the ground, don't hesitate to\nask me whatever you want!
Oh, thank you! I will never forget this!
